                            <comment id="27430" author="luke" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 04:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you actually have a situation where this causes a problem?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no need to set the password here as it is set by the LdapAuthenticationProvider when creating the final UserDetails object, complete with the authorities.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27432" author="vanwijngaarden" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2007 05:29:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found this issue as a result of the changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-595&quot; title=&quot;Allow for usage of passed user credentials for LDAP role lookup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-595&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-595&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where I want to use the passed user credentials in looking up the authorities in the LDAP tree. This was not possible since the password was not filled (yet).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27493" author="luke" created="Sun, 11 Nov 2007 05:38:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok. I see where you are coming from now. This sounds like a good option to have.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28336" author="luke" created="Fri, 7 Dec 2007 02:09:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Limited fix version to 1.0.x series. See comment in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-595&quot; title=&quot;Allow for usage of passed user credentials for LDAP role lookup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-595&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-595&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28338" author="luke" created="Fri, 7 Dec 2007 02:12:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Change made to 1.0.x branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
